title: Album Page, "Sketches from Coucy-le-Château", June 1, 1887
medium: Graphite on off-white wove paper tipped into binding with fabric
inscribed: Recto, in graphite, upper right corner: 10; lower right corner: 11; clockwise from top right: Coucy le Chateau / June 1st 1887; Gate to Town; Pitet Chateau
description: Vertical sheet depicting above a round masonry tower buttressed on the left side and with a pitched, crocketed spire behind it.  Below is a view through a large masonry gate into a streetscape.  The pointed arch opening is buried within the base of the walls of stair towers on either side.

tombstone.epitaph:
Album Page, "Sketches from Coucy-le-Château", June 1, 1887.
June 1, 1887. Graphite on off-white wove paper tipped into binding with fabric. Gift of Mrs. William Greenough. 1943-51-184.
